    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor powerplant. This example maintains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, delivering linear boost pressure through the entire power band without hesitation. The chassis remains structurally flawless, preserved with its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent diagnostic testing confirms optimal compression across all rotor faces, and the intricate 'rat's nest' of vacuum lines has been meticulously maintained to ensure peak pneumatic control. The five-speed manual transmission provides crisp engagement, and the cooling system has been thermally managed to prevent the heat-soak common in lesser examples. This is a purist-spec FD with a pristine undercarriage and zero modifications, representing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_3",
